HEADWORD: Interambulacrum
<hw>In`ter*am`bu*la"crum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> L. <plw>Interambulacra</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, E.
<plw>Interambulacrums</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>In echinoderms, one of the areas or zones intervening between two
